    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document defines a rendezvous extension for the Host Identity Protocol (HIP).  The rendezvous extension extends HIP and the HIP Registration Extension for initiating communication between HIP nodes via HIP rendezvous servers.  Rendezvous servers improve reachability and operation when HIP nodes are multihomed or mobile.  This document obsoletes RFC 5204.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
